Subject: [PATCH] =?UTF-8?q?phase9:=20wave=2016=20patch=200077=20=E2=80=94?=
 =?UTF-8?q?=20main.cpp=20kill-switch=20wiring=20(MAX=5FBPP=20follow-up)?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Wires the SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_PIXEL_FORMAT_8 kill-switch through to
SDL_HINT_DOS_MAX_BPP per /tmp/wave-16-spec.md §3.2. The hint must be
set BEFORE SDL_Init, so the kill-switch env-var has to be checked here
too — not just in Renderer::initVideo. wave-16-3 patch 0072 hardcoded
MAX_BPP="8"; without this follow-up, setting PIXEL_FORMAT_8=0 left
SDL3 in 8bpp framebuffer mode while the renderer produced RGB565
surfaces → format-mismatch + "Texture doesn't have a palette" spam in
the SDL_RenderTexture slow-path fall-through.

With this wiring:
  * SET SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_PIXEL_FORMAT_8=0 → MAX_BPP="16" end-to-end
    (true wave-15 baseline restoration; SDL3-DOS picks an RGB565 mode,
    engine produces RGB565 surfaces, wave-12 Lever B fast paths fire).
  * Anything else (unset, "1") → MAX_BPP="8" (wave-16 default-on).

Verified on DOSBox-X integration smoke for sub-phase 16.2:
  * Without the env var (default): indexed-mode ENABLED + 107 LUTs +
    MAX_BPP=8, fastpath idx8=31000/31000, cmod_general (idx=290) all
    INDEX8, no SDL_RenderTexture errors.
  * With SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_PIXEL_FORMAT_8=0: indexed-mode DISABLED +
    MAX_BPP=16, wave-15 RGB565 baseline restored, title menu renders
    pixel-identical to pre-wave-16.

Pairs with patch 0076 (attach master palette to window surface), which
was the other half of making indexed mode actually visible on DOSBox-X.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 src/main.cpp | 19 ++++++++++++++++++-
 1 file changed, 18 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/main.cpp b/src/main.cpp
index b4d7674..10c17dd 100644
--- a/src/main.cpp
+++ b/src/main.cpp
@@ -420,7 +420,24 @@ int main(int argc, char *argv[])
   // happens to find — that's expected and documented in the wave-16 spec
   // (/tmp/wave-16-spec.md §3) as a partial-integration state, not a 16.3
   // bug. See docs/PHASE9-WAVE-14-PLAN.md §5 for the wave-16 plan.
-  SDL_SetHintWithPriority(SDL_HINT_DOS_MAX_BPP, "8", SDL_HINT_OVERRIDE);
+  //
+  // Patch 0076 (Phase 9 wave 16 sub-phase 16.2 follow-up): wire the
+  // SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_PIXEL_FORMAT_8 kill-switch through to MAX_BPP per
+  // wave-16-spec §3.2. The hint must be set BEFORE SDL_Init, so the
+  // kill-switch env-var has to be checked here too — not just in
+  // Renderer::initVideo. If the SDL hint says 8 but the renderer thinks
+  // 16, the framebuffer is INDEX8 and engine RGB565 surfaces hit format-
+  // mismatch failures (the "Texture doesn't have a palette" spam observed
+  // mid-integration). With this wiring SET SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_PIXEL_FORMAT_8=0
+  // restores the wave-15 baseline end-to-end (16bpp framebuffer + 16bpp
+  // engine surfaces); anything else (unset, "1") keeps wave-16 8bpp on.
+  {
+    const char *fmt8_kill = SDL_getenv("SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_PIXEL_FORMAT_8");
+    const bool indexed_disabled = (fmt8_kill && fmt8_kill[0] == '0' && fmt8_kill[1] == 0);
+    SDL_SetHintWithPriority(SDL_HINT_DOS_MAX_BPP,
+                            indexed_disabled ? "16" : "8",
+                            SDL_HINT_OVERRIDE);
+  }
 
   // Patch 0045 (Phase 9 lever 1, 2026-04-26): prefer LFB over banked at the
   // SDL3-DOS LFB-vs-banked decision (vendor/SDL/src/video/dos/SDL_dosmodes.c).
